.TH "dev_addr_add" 9 "dev_addr_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_addr_add \- Add a device address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dev_addr_add
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const unsigned char *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned char addr_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device
.IP "addr" 12
address to add
.IP "addr_type" 12
address type

Add a device address to the device or increase the reference count if
it already exists.

The caller must hold the rtnl_mutex.
